     <font class="TallRed">esialb you will enjoy this.<a name="109261480484697393">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          For those who wondered how it was that the creator of the Walkman, which is by all means, the mother and creator of portable audio, missed the market on the portable MP3 player, here is further evidence why. It looks like Sony's "iPod killer" isn't. It is smaller and has a longer battery life, but that is about it. The iPod is still the king of the market. The interface sucks, the software sucks, and it's download service doesn't even come close to that of iTunes. Apple will hit the market this year with the iPod 4, which will offer a 50% gain in the battery life, and a much more streamlined interface. When will Sony learn? Its box doesn't play MP3's, and uses a proprietary encoding system. The only thing that even comes close to dethroning the MP3 as of yet has been the WMV, and that quite frankly is ONLY because of the ability for MS to float above the drwoning waters due to its Media Player software. You may be able to make an argument for Real Audio files, but then again, probably not. Sony uses a new Encoding called ATRAC, which is supposed to have better sonic quality, but in order to load the box, you have to use Sony's software to convert your MP3's. Oh, that sounds so fun doesn't it! From one report I found, the software takes forever, and if a file will not convert, it not doesn't tell you why, it even fails to tell you which songs didn't make the cut.<br /><br />Here are some comparisons I dug up.<h3 align="center" class="boldThirteen"><a name="APPLE"></a>Apple Challenge</h3><br /><table style="border:1px solid #000000;" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" width="95%"><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven">&nbsp; </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven"><b>iPod</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven"><b>Sony<br />NW-HD1</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven"><b>iPod<br />mini</b> </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Capacity</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">20GB </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">20GB </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">4GB </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Price</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">$299  </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">$399  </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">$249  </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Dimensions</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">4.1&quot; x 2.4&quot; x .57&quot; </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">3.6&quot; x 2.5&quot; x .56&quot; </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">3.6&quot; x 2&quot; x .5&quot; </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Weight (Ounces)</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">5.6 </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">3.8 </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">3.6 </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Formats Supported</b> </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">AAC, MP3, Audible, WAV, and others </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">ATRAC3, ATRAC3plus </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">AAC, MP3, Audible, WAV, and others </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Music Store Supported</b>  </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">iTunes </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">Connect </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">iTunes </td></tr><br /><tr><td valign="top" class="plnEleven"><b>Claimed Battery Life</b>  </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">Up to 12 hours </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">Up to 30 hours </td><td align="LEFT" valign="TOP" class="plnEleven">Up to 8 hours </td></tr></table><br /><br /><i>edited by FSEVN.</i> Watch your table widths, people.<br />
